## Multi-projectile damage model implementation

Buckshot requires **per-pellet hit calculation** rather than single-projectile damage. For each of 9 pellets:

1. **Calculate pattern center**: Apply base accuracy deviation from aim point
2. **Determine spread radius**: Base spread × (distance/10) × choke modifier
3. **Randomize pellet position**: Each pellet falls randomly within spread circle
4. **Check hit registration**: Is pellet within target hitbox?
5. **Apply damage**: ~40-50 damage per pellet hitting vital zones

**Expected damage by range** (all pellets on target):

| Range | Pellets Hitting | Buckshot Damage | Slug Damage |
|-------|-----------------|-----------------|-------------|
| 5m | 9/9 | 360-405 | 240-255 |
| 15m | 8-9/9 | 320-405 | 230-245 |
| 25m | 5-7/9 | 200-315 | 215-235 |
| 40m | 2-4/9 | 80-180 | 190-210 |
| 60m | 0-2/9 | 0-90 | 160-180 |

Shotguns should deliver **one-shot-kill potential within 15 meters** when most pellets connect, but suffer severe effectiveness degradation beyond **40 meters**—creating clear role definition against rifles and SMGs. Magazine capacity limitations (4-8 rounds) and long individual reload times (0.5-0.6 seconds per shell) provide balancing vulnerabilities during extended engagements.
